# EpiCloud

EpiCloud is a PowerShell module that calls the PaaS deployment API. When working in **EpiCloud**:

## Structure

- **source/Public/** – Public cmdlets (e.g. `Start-EpiDeployment.ps1`, `Complete-EpiDeployment.ps1`)
- **source/Private/** – Helpers (API requests, auth, encoding)
- **source/Tests/** – Pester unit and integration tests

## API Flow

1. `Connect-EpiCloud` – authenticate and set session
2. `Start-EpiDeployment`, `Complete-EpiDeployment`, `Reset-EpiDeployment` – deployment lifecycle
3. `Get-EpiDeployment`, `Get-EpiDatabaseExport` – status and exports

## Contracts

- Parameters (ClientKey, ClientSecret, ProjectId, DeploymentPackage, etc.) map to PaaS API
- Changing parameters may require PaaS API and ARCHITECTURE.md updates
